article.headline: American 76, Lafayette 74
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP) -- Andre Ingram scored 20 points and hit the game-winning jumper with .4 seconds to play to lift American to a 76-74 win over Lafayette Saturday afternoon. Ingram's last-second jumper bailed the Eagles (9-6, 2-1) out a near collapse as Lafayette (5-10, 1-2) rallied from six points down with 42 seconds left to tie the game. Linas Lekavicius, who scored a season-high 14 points, missed two free throws with 21 seconds left. After the missed shots, Lafayette's Marcus Harley hit a jumper, followed by a steal by Paul Cummins, who was fouled as he made a layup with 13.7 seconds left tying the game at 74. However, he missed the go-ahead free throw, giving Ingram the chance to catch the ball on the right wing and sink the desperate leaning jumper to win it. Sean Knitter scored 17 points off the bench to lead the Leopards, including three 3-pointers that helped trim American's 12-point second-half lead down to two with six minutes to play. Harley finished with 13 points for Lafayette. American, which has now won three straight, shot just 14-for-31 from the foul line in the second half and turned the ball over 16 times.
